result.execSummary:
The defendant Cole D. Nimphius was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cole D. Nimphius is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cole D. Nimphius was found guilty of Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.
  • Cole D. Nimphius was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that all parties have received the revocation packet.  Atty Gumz received a copy of the revocation packet and have no changes at this time.  

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.  Victim is here and does not wish to make a statement to the court.
Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments.
Father makes a statement to the court.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 2:  Court orders 9 months in the Marquette County Jail w/huber; consecutive to any other sentence
Ct. 3:  Court orders 90 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber; concurrent to Ct. 2
Defendant is remanded into custody
Credit = 98 days
Sentencing hearing on revocation on January 6, 2017 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Counts 2 & 3.  Ct. 1 to be dismissed.  Atty Johnson agrees and enters a No Contest plea.  Defendant agrees.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
  Atty Hendee relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Counts 2 & 3.  Ct. 1 to be dismissed.

Atty Hendee asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.
Atty Johnson makes a statement and asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.

BY THE COURT: Counts 2 & 3:  Withhold Sentence; 2 years Probation with conditions:
Court Costs = $243.00 on each count
Mr. Nimphius is to live at Care Wisconsin Group home in Wautoma or a similar place that is approved by the Agent
Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent
No contact with Nicole Marshall

Ct. 1 to be dismissed.
Defendant is to report directly to the Wautoma DOC office.

Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the parties are very close to resolution and is asking for one more reset.
Atty Johnson agrees and states that the defendant is supposed to reside in a group home for supervision and is working on that.

BY THE COURT:  Set for Plea/Sentencing.
bond continued.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 20, 2015 at 11:15 am.
Return date on April 1, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Johnson states that there has been some brief discussions on the case and most likely be resolved but there are some houseing issues yet.  Atty Johnson asks for 60 days to be reset.

BY THE COURT:  Reset.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for April 1, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Return date on January 21, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that there has been discussions on the matter.  Atty Johnson needs to gather some medical information and needs more time and asks that a Status be set.

BY THE COURT:  Set for Return.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for January 21, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
PETITION FOR LEAVE TO FILE ADDITIONAL MOTIONS
Return date on November 12, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
*No contact with Nicole Marshall, her family or her residence

Defendant Cole D. Nimphius in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Johnson states that the Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Atty Hendee requests a $5,000 cash bond with conditions.
No contact with Nicole Marshall, her family or her residence.  Atty Johnson responds and requests a $1,000 cash bond.
Atty Hendee responds and requests the $5,000 cash bond as requested.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $5,000 cash bond with conditions:
*No contact with Nicole Marshall, her family or her residence

Atty Johnson waives the time limits for the Prelim and requests a Return date.
